SIMPLE: froward
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Froward
<hw>Fro"ward</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Fro</ets> +
<ets>-ward</ets>. See <er>Fro</er>, and cf. <er>Fromward</er>.]</ety>
<def>Not willing to yield or comply with what is required or is
reasonable; perverse; disobedient; peevish; <as>as, a <ex>froward</ex>
child</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>froward</qex> man soweth strife.</q> <rj><qau>Prov. xvi.
28.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>froward</qex> retention of custom is as turbulent a thing
as innovation.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Untoward; wayward; unyielding; ungovernable:
refractory; obstinate; petulant; cross; peevish. See
<er>Perverse</er>.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Fro"ward*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Fro"ward*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frower</ent>⟦br⟧
